page.title: 05WILDLIFE
page.content: In Northend there is quite a lot of wildlife.One of the small species of mammals is the mouse.The house mouse is quite common it lives in houses. They eat any food drop by man.They are usually coloured grey-brown or they can be white.A tree which is not common at all is the elm.They died in 1970 from a disease spread by elm bark beetles. Some elms could reach 30 metres in height. Another small wild mammal is the rabbit.It can be domestic as well as wild.Wild rabbits have a short fur which is grey_brown.The fur under the body is white. They have a short white and brown tail.They have long strong back legs which makes them fast.They also have long ears. They live in burrows.
